    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1R"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Mobile</placeName>
                <date>May 2nd 1853</date>
            </p>
            <p>Dear friend,</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Enclosed you will find <persName>St John
                    Paverski<add>?</add></persName><lb/> check on Bk N. America your favor for<lb/>
                Three hundred &amp; fifty Dols. ($350)—the<lb/> odd fifty you will please dispose of
                as<lb/> follows—Six Dols. To <persName>Geo &amp; Jas Benners</persName> the<lb/>
                liquor men in <placeName>2nd below Race St.</placeName> to cover<lb/> a small
                balance of that Amt. against me.<lb/> Thirty five 30/100 Dols—please pay to
                    <persName>Wm<lb/> Hoskins</persName> when he calls on you for it. I<lb/> shall
                draw on you in his favor for the<lb/> amt. So as not to trouble you to go to him.<lb/>
                <persName>Hoskins</persName> is the man who made my Dray<lb/> the balance of the
                fifty; Eight 70/100 please hand<lb/> to <persName>Mrs O.</persName> to get
                    <persName>Nell</persName> a dress or any article of<lb/> clothing she may
                prefer. The Rest of the<lb/> check you know about from my letter<lb/> last night. I
                have nothing to add to<lb/> it but beg you not to forget the “two bad<lb/>
                paymasters„ I have invariably found payment in<lb/> advance to be detrimental to
                both parties—but<lb/> prompt payment as the work is done will<lb/> secure you
                willing workmen &amp; good work.<lb/> With my <sic>sincer</sic> love and assurances
                of<lb/> my constant good wishes for your health<lb/> &amp; prosperity Believe me
                Ever yr friend</p>
            <p rend="indent(9)"><persName role="author">SWolff</persName>.</p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <placeName>Philad</placeName>
            </p>
            <pb n="1V"/>
            <p>I would have added to the within the<lb/> amt due you from <persName>Jones</persName>
                congregation<lb/> but have not collected it yet—I miss<lb/> him every time I go
                there &amp; when we<lb/> meet we <sic>cant</sic> get hold of the Sec.<lb/> it shall
                come along shortly though</p>
        </body>
